Conclusion for Condition for Use: Sea level pressure is continuous quantitative variable. This data is most likely representative of daily weather data in Denver during 2018. The data is independent because the weather of one day likely does not impact the weather of the next. Based on the figure above the residuals seem to have a constant $\sigma^2$. The residuals are approximately normally distributed with a mean of zero, satisfying the assumption of normality. Furthermore, the predictor variables exhibit low multicollinearity, as evidenced by the dispersion of residuals, indicating that the predictors are not highly correlated. These conditions validate the use of the linear regression model data set.

```{r}
vif(model.1)
```

Multicollinearity: For the most part, there is no correlation for visibility, wind speed, and snow depth. However, temperature and dew point have moderate correlation between a given predictor variable and other predictor variables in the model, but this is often not severe enough to require attention, being valued at less than 5.

After assessing the assumptions, there appears to be no clear violations of the conditions for use, therefore we will continue with model selection without the need for transformations.

## Model Selection: First Order Model

### Backward Elimination and AIC

```{r}
bAIC <- stepAIC(model.1,direction ="backward",trace =FALSE)
summary(bAIC)
```

### Backward Elimination and BIC

```{r}
bBIC <- stepAIC(model.1,direction="backward",k=log(nrow(gsod.data.clean)),trace=FALSE)
summary(bBIC)
```

### Forward Selection and AIC

```{r}
intercept<-lm(SLP~1,data=gsod.data.clean)
```

```{r}
fAIC <- stepAIC(intercept,direction ="forward",scope =list(upper =model.1),trace =FALSE)
summary(fAIC)
```

### Forward Selection and BIC

```{r}
fBIC <- stepAIC(intercept,direction ="forward",scope =list(upper =model.1),k=log(nrow(gsod.data.clean)),trace =FALSE)
summary(fBIC)
```

### Stepwise Selection and AIC

```{r}
sAIC <- stepAIC(intercept,direction ="both",scope =list(upper =model.1),trace =FALSE)
summary(sAIC)
```

### Stepwise Selection and BIC

```{r}
sBIC <- stepAIC(intercept,direction ="both",scope =list(upper =model.1),k=log(nrow(gsod.data.clean)),trace =FALSE)
summary(sBIC)
```

